# Charte de Développement Easy Rental

Source officielle : `Charte de Développement et contraintes Technologiques.pdf` (racine dépôt) — règle complète : `.cursor/rules/charte-officielle-v01.mdc`.

## Naming (§1)
- Charte PDF : variables **snake_case** ; méthodes **camelCase**
- **Java (ce projet)** : variables/champs **camelCase** ; méthodes **camelCase**
- DB (Liquibase) & JSON/API : **snake_case** (`user_name`, `order_date`)
- Constants: **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** (`MAX_SIZE`, `DEPOSIT_RATE`)
- Classes: **PascalCase** (`CustomerService`)
- Packages: lowercase, no accents (`com.yowyob.easyrental.rental`)
- Interfaces: no `I` prefix (`PaymentProcessor`, not `IPaymentProcessor`)

## Code organization (§2)
- One public class per file
- Max line length: **120 characters**
- Indentation: **4 spaces** (no tabs)
- Opening brace on same line: `if (condition) {`
- **No wildcard imports** (`import java.util.*` forbidden)

## Documentation (§3)
- Every public class: Javadoc header with description, `@author`, `@since`
- Public methods: `@param`, `@return`, `@throws`
- Comments in **English only**

## Exceptions (§4)
- Use specific exceptions, never generic `Exception`/`RuntimeException` in business code
- Error messages in **English**
- Propagate only when relevant; handle locally otherwise

## Best practices (§5)
- SOLID principles; Controller → UseCase → Port (hexagonal)
- No magic numbers — use constants in `shared/constants/`
- Prefer primitives over wrappers unless needed
- Use `Optional` or reactive `Mono` for absent values
- Never log passwords, tokens, or sensitive data

## Tests (§6)
- JUnit 5 for every new feature
- Minimum **80% coverage** (JaCoCo enforced)
- Test names: `shouldReturnErrorWhenInputIsInvalid`
- Use Checkstyle, PMD, SonarLint

## Git (§7)
- One feature = one branch: `feature/`, `bugfix/`, `hotfix/`
- Commits in English, imperative mood: `Add payment gateway integration`
